{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, for any possibility X ∈ F ℘, the set R ℘ i (X) = {Y ∈ S ℘ | XR ℘ i Y } has a maximum in ⟨S ℘, ⊑ ℘ ⟩, i.e., a single possibility f i (X) of which all possibilities accessible from X are refinements, namely f i (X) = R i [X].",
    "This makes possible a functional semantics for the modality □ i, which we may retain even as we generalize away from powerset possibilizations.",
    "Definition 4.25 (Quasi-Functional and Functional Possibility Frames).",
    "A quasi-functional possibility frame is a possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ satisfying:1.",
    "R-max -if R i (x) ̸ = ∅, then R i (x) has a maximum in ⟨S, ⊑⟩.An extended quasi-functional possibility frame is an extended possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, ⊥, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ (Definition 4.19) satisfying:2."
  ]
}